    <p>keep an open mind to all th­ese ideas,” he promised.</p>
    <p>The MPs who spoke yes­ter­day did not dis­pute the Deputy Prime Min­is­ter’s call for Sin­ga­pore to re­main open. But what they asked for is a fun­da­men­tal change in the ap­proach to poli­cies and pol­i­tics.</p>
    <p>On poli­cies, their fo­cus was on for­eign man­power.</p>
    <p>Ms Foo Mee Har (West Coast GRC) stated starkly that Sin­ga­pore­ans should be given pri­or­ity, and not just be fairly con­sid­ered, for jobs they can do.</p>

